a%20handshake%2C%20a%20single%20paycheck%20supported%20three%20kids%20with%20two%20cars%20and%20a%20white%20picket%20fence%20to%20boot%2C%20and%20you%20could%20work%20your%20way%20through%20college%20without%20going%20into%20debt.%20The%20boomers%20had%20it%20great%2C%20the%20argument%20goes%2C%20but%20then%20they%20went%20and%20screwed%20it%20all%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20instinct%20is%20wrong.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20baby%20boomers%20didn't%20have%20it%20easy%3A%20The%20America%20they%20grew%20up%20in%20was%20poorer%2C%20less%20educated%2C%20less%20healthy%2C%20and%20more%20unfair%20than%20the%20society%20we%20live%20in%20today.%20And%20for%20all%20the%20flak%20the%20older%20generation%20gets%2C%20the%20boomers%20have%20by%20and%20large%20left%20America%20a%20better%20place%20than%20how%20they%20found%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20to%20say%20that%20the%20boomers%20are%20handing%20young%20people%20a%20utopia.%20Plenty%20of%20challenges%20still%20need%20to%20be%20solved%20%E2%80%94%20from%20a%20housing%20shortage%20and%20high%20inequality%20to%20the%20dangers%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20rising%20political%20instability%20%E2%80%94%20and%20many%20of%20them%20were%20partly%20caused%20by%20the%20boomers'%20decisions.%20But%20we%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20solve%20those%20problems%20by%20lying%20to%20ourselves%20about%20the%20past%20or%20the%20progress%20we've%20made%20over%20the%20past%2070%20years.%20It's%20time%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20gave%20the%20boomers%20their%20due%20credit%2C%20even%20as%20they%20try%20to%20fix%20some%20of%20the%20messes%20they've%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThings%20are%20better%20now%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20be%20envious%20when%20viewing%20the%20midcentury%20Norman%20Rockwell%20paintings%20of%20the%20beautiful%20family%20sitting%20in%20their%20lovely%20home%20preparing%20to%20dig%20into%20a%20massive%20meal.%20But%20I%20have%20a%20secret%20to%20tell%20you%3A%20On%20a%20statistical%20basis%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20you're%20richer%20than%20them.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThat's%20because%2C%20despite%20the%20protestations%20from%20the%20commentariat%2C%20the%20simple%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20US%20is%20a%20vastly%20wealthier%20and%20more%20productive%20country%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20encompassing%20way%20to%20measure%20this%20is%20real%20gross%20domestic%20product%20per%20capita%2C%20which%20takes%20the%20entire%20economic%20output%20of%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20all%20the%20goods%20we%20make%2C%20from%20cars%20to%20houses%20to%20food%2C%20and%20all%20the%20services%20we%20buy%20from%20each%20other%2C%20from%20doctor%20visits%20to%20education%20%E2%80%94%20and%20divides%20it%20up%20by%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20live%20in%20the%20country.%20Importantly%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Breal%26quot%3B%20part%20adjusts%20for%20inflation%3A%20We're%20looking%20at%20the%20actual%20quantity%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20bought%20and%20sold%20without%20being%20skewed%20by%20the%20upward%20drift%20of%20prices.%20In%20effect%2C%20it%20tells%20us%20that%20we%20make%20and%20do%20far%20more%20things%20than%20we%20did%20a%20half%20century%20ago.%20Since%20World%20War%20II%2C%20real%20GDP%20per%20capita%20has%20steadily%20and%20inexorably%20grown%20outside%20brief%20recessions.%20There%20are%20three%20times%20as%20many%20goods%20and%20services%20produced%20in%20the%20US%20available%20per%20person%20now%20as%20there%20were%20in%20the%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FSBWVG%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Real%20GDP%20per%20capita%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20looking%20at%20GDP%20per%20capita%20doesn't%20necessarily%20show%20who's%20gaining%20from%20that%20rising%20tide.%20To%20better%20understand%20how%20individuals%20and%20families%20are%20experiencing%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20look%20at%20wages%2C%20income%2C%20and%20wealth.%20These%20three%20measures%20can%20give%20us%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20how%20people's%20finances%20are%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20there%20are%20wages%2C%20which%20measure%20people's%20paychecks%20and%20salaries%20from%20their%20jobs.%20Real%20average%20hourly%20wages%20for%20nonsupervisory%20and%20production%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20frontline%20workers%20instead%20of%20managers%20or%20business%20owners%20%E2%80%94%20slid%20fairly%20dramatically%20from%20the%20'70s%20through%20the%20mid-'90s.%20But%20since%20that%20time%2C%20wages%20have%20steadily%20increased.%20Even%20with%20the%20recent%20bout%20of%20high%20inflation%2C%20the%20strong%20labor%20market%20has%20pushed%20wages%20for%20frontline%20workers%20higher%20than%20they've%20been%20since%20the%20'70s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F7cHcl%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Real%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20for%20production%20and%20nonsupervisory%20employees%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20is%20household%20income%20%E2%80%94%20the%20total%20amount%20of%20money%20the%20typical%20family%20makes%20from%20everyone's%20jobs%20and%20businesses%20in%20a%20year.%20While%20recessions%20have%20led%20to%20fits%20and%20starts%2C%20the%20typical%20family%20is%20more%20affluent%20than%2040%20years%20ago.%20Median%20household%20income%20after%20adjusting%20for%20inflation%20in%202022%20was%2031%25%20higher%20than%20in%201984%2C%20meaning%20families%20have%20more%20money%20to%20work%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDfMNc%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Median%20real%20household%20income%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20there's%20wealth%2C%20which%20tracks%20a%20family's%20assets%2C%20such%20as%20real%20estate%2C%20financial%20investments%2C%20and%20checking%20accounts%20minus%20their%20debt.%20Once%20again%2C%20families%20are%20better%20off%20by%20this%20measure%20than%20when%20the%20boomers%20were%20becoming%20dominant%20in%20the%20economy.%20Real%20household%20net%20worth%20fell%20dramatically%20after%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%20because%20of%20the%20collapse%20in%20home%20prices%20but%20steadily%20recovered%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20before%20skyrocketing%20between%202019%20and%202022%20as%20home%20values%20and%20stock%20prices%20surged%20and%20the%20country%20healed%20from%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FMPhOt%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Median%20real%20household%20net%20worth%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20most%20measures%20of%20financial%20health%2C%20the%20typical%20American%20is%20doing%20much%20better%20today%20than%20in%20the%20decades%20when%20the%20boomers%20were%20coming%20up.%20Of%20course%2C%20money%20isn't%20the%20only%20way%20to%20evaluate%20a%20life.%20But%20by%20many%20nonfinancial%20measures%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20have%20it%20better%20than%20their%20parents'%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20living%20much%20longer%20than%20when%20the%20boomers%20were%20growing%20up.%20Despite%20a%20historic%20drop%20in%20life%20expec