%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20racial%20inequalities%20at%20work%20have%20declined%20over%20the%20past%20half%20century.%20Historically%2C%20the%20share%20of%20Black%20Americans%20with%20a%20job%20has%20been%20lower%20than%20that%20of%20white%20Americans%2C%20but%20that%20gap%20has%20narrowed%20since%20the%20Great%20Recession%20and%20was%20nearly%20closed%20as%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FHeAC0%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Employment-to-population%20ratio%20by%20race%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20also%20been%20broad%20qualitative%20improvements%20across%20a%20plethora%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20available%20to%20the%20average%20American.%20Cars%20are%20safer%20and%20more%20fuel-efficient%20than%20they%20were%20a%20half%20century%20ago%2C%20entertainment%20options%20have%20exploded%2C%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20internet%20means%20that%20we%20now%20all%20have%20access%20to%20the%20sum%20total%20of%20human%20knowledge%20in%20our%20pockets%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECredit%20where%20credit%20is%20due%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simple%20fact%20is%20that%20America%20is%20a%20much%20more%20broadly%20wealthy%20society%20than%20it%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%20There%20are%20plenty%20of%20reasons%20we're%20better%20off%20nowadays%2C%20as%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20technological%2C%20social%2C%20financial%2C%20and%20broad%20economic%20changes%20have%20happened%20under%20the%20boomers'%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20for%20America's%20growing%20prosperity%20is%20ongoing%20technological%20improvements%20%E2%80%94%20much%20of%20which%20was%20developed%20by%20the%20boomers.%20Developments%20in%20industrial%20automation%20and%20computers%20have%20greatly%20accelerated%20productivity%2C%20a%20measure%20of%20the%20amount%20of%20economic%20activity%20per%20worker.%20An%20accountant%20working%20in%20Excel%20can%20balance%20a%20company's%20books%20in%20seconds%2C%20while%20working%20it%20out%20on%20paper%20would%20take%20hours.%20These%20improvements%20let%20us%20produce%20more%2C%20meaning%20a%20much%20larger%20economic%20pie%20is%20available%20to%20be%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FdZs65%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Total%20factor%20productivity%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20important%20boomer%20contribution%20to%20our%20prosperity%20is%20our%20largely%20stable%20and%20increasingly%20open%20world.%20While%20globalized%20trade%20has%20hurt%20certain%20sectors%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it's%20contributed%20to%20lower%20prices%20and%20more%20widely%20available%20goods.%20America%20has%20become%20a%20more%20egalitarian%20and%20open%20society%20after%20the%20civil-rights%20and%20feminist%20movements%20of%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20which%20opened%20the%20doors%20to%20greater%20economic%20and%20social%20participation%20for%20traditionally%20excluded%20groups%20and%20created%20a%20vast%20pool%20of%20talent%20to%20add%20to%20that%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEverything%20isn't%20perfect%2C%20but%20it's%20better%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20every%20Gen%20Zer%20and%20millennial%20needs%20to%20go%20up%20to%20the%20boomers%20in%20their%20life%20and%20bow%20down%20to%20their%20benevolence.%20The%20%26quot%3BMe%26quot%3B%20generation%20also%20left%20their%20progeny%20with%20plenty%20of%20problems.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20glaring%20issues%20is%20the%20growth%20of%20economic%20inequality%3A%20Despite%20gains%20in%20wages%2C%20much%20of%20the%20great%20wealth%20created%20by%20the%20boomers%20has%20flowed%20to%20the%20top.%20One%20way%20to%20define%20inequality%20is%20to%20look%20at%20how%20the%20share%20of%20the%20country's%20wealth%20held%20by%20those%20at%20the%20top%20compares%20with%20the%20middle%20class.%20Since%20roughly%201998%2C%20the%20top%201%25%20has%20held%20more%20of%20the%20nation's%20wealth%20than%20the%20middle%2040%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDd6Tu%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Wealth%20share%20in%20the%20US%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAdmittedly%2C%20there%20are%20some%20encouraging%20signs%20that%20the%20inequality%20trend%20could%20be%20reversing.%20Over%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20wage%20growth%20has%20been%20disproportionately%20concentrated%20among%20low-income%20workers%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20compression%20in%20income%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20area%20where%20the%20boomers%20have%20left%20the%20country%20worse%20off%20is%20housing.%20Boomers%20have%20consistently%20passed%20laws%20to%20make%20building%20housing%20harder%2C%20leaving%20the%20country%20with%20a%20structural%20housing%20deficit.%20The%20consequence%3F%20Soaring%20housing%20costs.%20A%20typical%20house%20cost%20a%20little%20under%20three%20times%20the%20typical%20family's%20income%20in%20the%20mid-'60s%3B%20after%20the%20recent%20post-pandemic%20run-up%20in%20housing%20prices%2C%20that%20figure%20was%20nearly%20five%20times%20family%20income%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFu7ws%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Housing%20affordability%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20boomers%20have%20handed%20off%20other%20deep%20problems%20that%20the%20younger%20generations%20will%20have%20to%20solve.%20The%20climate%20crisis%20threatens%20to%20undermine%20our%20collective%20prosperity%2C%20COVID-19%20has%20shown%20that%20a%20highly%20globalized%20world%20is%20susceptible%20to%20dangerous%20pandemics%2C%20and%20rising%20political%20polarization%20is%20challenging%20one%20of%20the%20core%20prerequisites%20of%20a%20wealthy%2C%20stable%2C%20and%20democratic%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20is%20a%20much%20different%20place%20from%20it%20was%20when%20the%20boomers%20were%20young.%20There%20are%20problems%2C%20yes%2C%20but%20for%20Americans%2C%20the%20country%20is%20largely%20a%20much-better%20place.%20The%20siren%20song%20of%20nostalgia%20reaches%20out%20to%20most%20generations%20in%20most%20times%20and%20places%20across%20history.%20Millennials%20and%20Zoomers%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20ignore%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fandy-kiersz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAndy%20Kiersz%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20quantitative%20editor%20for%20Business%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-baby-boomers-stop-complaining-wealth-housing-economy-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704190922000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658f27ffec62ab5daf7fb279%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-baby-boomers-stop-complaining-wealth-housing-economy-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22They%20made%20America%20richer%2C%20promoted%20equal%20rights%2C%20and%20invented%20the%20internet.%20Why%20don't%20boomers%20get%20any%20love%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22akiersz%40businessinsider.com%20(Andy%20Kiersz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-baby-boomers-stop-complaining-wealth-housing-economy-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWon't%20Have%20Rs%2010%20For%20Tea%26quot%3B%3A%20Truckers%20Protest%20Near%20Delhi%20Against%20New%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETruck%20drivers%20and%20cab%20operators%20across%20the%20country%20are%20protesting%20against%20the%20provisions%20covering%20hit-and-run%20cases%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20that%20is%20set%20to%20replace%20the%20colonial-era%20Indian%20Penal%20Code.%20Under%20the%20new%20law%2C%20hit-and-run%20cases%20can%20attract%20up%20to%2010%20years%20in%20jail%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%207%20lakh%20if%20the%20driver%20flees%20the%20accident%20spot%20and%20does%20not%20inform%20cops.%20Currently%2C%20hit-and-run%20accidents%20are%20covered%20by%20IPC's%20Section%20304A%20and%20attracts%20a%20jail%20term%20that%20may%20extend%20to%20two%20years%20and%20an%20unspecified%20fine%20or%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%2C%20which%20has%20received%20the%20President's%20assent%20after%20clearing%20Parliament%2C%20has%20sparked%20widespread%20protests%20by%20truck%20drivers.%20The%20protests%20have%20hit%20fuel%20supply%20lines%20in%20some%20areas.%20Several%20other%20places%20are%20witnessing%20panic%20buying%20of%20fuel%20as%20people%20fear%20it%20may%20run%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20Ghaziabad%20today%2C%20protesters%20stopped%20auto-rickshaws%20and%20tractors%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20turn%20around.%20In%20one%20of%20the%20videos%2C%20they%20were%20seen%20stopping%20a%20pick-up%20van%20and%20putting%20a%20garland%20of%20shoes%20around%20the%20driver's%20neck.%20They%20were%20heard%20asking%20why%20he%20is%20driving%20and%20not%20protesting%20against%20the%20law%20that%20will%20%26quot%3Bnot%20even%20spare%20Rs%2010%20for%20tea%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20bus%20depot%20in%20the%20area%2C%20state%20transport%20buses%20have%20been%20grounded%20as%20their%20drivers%20joined%20the%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protesters%20described%20the%20new%20law%20as%20%26quot%3Bblind%26quot%3B.%20Dinesh%20Singh%2C%20who%20said%20he%20is%20an%20office-bearer%20in%20an%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20transport%20association%2C%20said%20the%20drivers%20are%20demanding%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20law.%20%26quot%3BWe%20barely%20make%206000%20rupees%20a%20month.%20How%20will%20we%20pay%20Rs%207%20lakh%20in%20fine%3F%20And%20if%20we%20go%20to%20jail%20for%2010%20years%2C%20who%20will%20feed%20our%20children%3F%20We%20will%20block%20all%20traffic%20movement%20if%20our%20demands%20are%20not%20accepted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protesters%20also%20questioned%20who%20will%20protect%20them%20from%20mob%20assault%20if%20they%20stop%20at%20the%20accident%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPintu%2C%20a%20driver%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20saying%20that%20we%20should%20stop%20and%20rush%20the%20victim%20to%20a%20hospital.%20But%20the%20moment%20we%20stop%2C%20people%20will%20kill%20us.%20They%20will%20lock%20us%20inside%20and%20set%20the%20vehicle%20on%20fire.%20This%20is%20the%20law%20here.%26quot%3B%20Smaller%20vehicles%2C%20he%20said%2C%20suddenly%20switch%20lanes%20and%20brake%20abruptly.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20are%20driving%20a%20loaded%20vehicle%2C%20we%20cannot%20apply%20brakes%20suddenly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Singh%20said%20the%20situation%20is%20such%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20government%20will%20kill%20us%20if%20we%20run%2C%20the%20public%20will%20kill%20if%20we%20stop%26quot%3B.%C2%A0The%20drivers%20said%20no%20driver%20wants%20anyone%20to%20die%20in%20accidents%2C%20but%20this%20la