F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20black%20man%20in%20Fanon%20is%20a%20manifestation%20of%20the%20oppressed%2C%20allied%20to%20all%20the%20other%20oppressed.%20So%2C%20what%20would%20it%20mean%20today%20to%20say%20that%20the%20aim%20is%20nothing%20less%20than%20to%20liberate%20the%20oppressed%20%E2%80%93%20the%20communities%20of%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%2C%20Muslims%2C%20and%20women%2C%20among%20others%20%E2%80%93%20from%20themselves%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E**%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%2C%20Fanon%20also%20describes%2C%20almost%20in%20passing%2C%20how%20to%20identify%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccolonised%20people%E2%80%9D%3A%20they%20are%20people%20in%20whom%20an%20inferiority%20complex%20has%20taken%20root%2C%20whose%20%E2%80%9Clocal%20cultural%20originality%20has%20been%20committed%20to%20the%20grave%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20very%20distinctive%20happens%20here%3A%20colonialism%20is%20described%20in%20psychological%20terms%2C%20or%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20violence%20that%20the%20colonised%20also%20inflict%20on%20themselves.%20(Fanon%20declares%20in%20the%20introduction%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20analysis%20we%20are%20undertaking%20is%20psychological.%E2%80%9D)%20He%20is%20acutely%20aware%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20this%20violence%20originates%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20in%20the%20external%20world%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20precisely%20what%20makes%20it%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20self-inflicted%20dimension%20is%20what%20is%20distinctive%20to%20psychological%20colonialism%2C%20and%20to%20psychic%20violence%20more%20broadly.%20Unlike%20socioeconomic%20and%20political%20colonialism%20and%20violence%2C%20which%20can%20remain%20primarily%20external%2C%20psychic%20violence%20embeds%20itself%20in%20the%20soul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20embeds%20itself%20in%20the%20soul%20of%20both%20the%20oppressor%20and%20the%20oppressed.%20So%2C%20unlike%20socioeconomic%20and%20political%20violence%2C%20psychic%20violence%20dehumanises%20not%20only%20the%20oppressed%20but%20also%20the%20oppressor.%20This%20dehumanisation%20is%20why%20Fanon%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20black%20man%20wants%20to%20be%20white.%20The%20white%20man%20is%20desperately%20trying%20to%20achieve%20the%20rank%20of%20man.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFanon%20is%20hardly%20alone%20in%20underscoring%20the%20psychological%20dimension%20of%20colonial%20power%2C%20and%20of%20domination%2C%20more%20broadly.%20Much%20of%20the%20same%20theme%20runs%20through%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20writing.%C2%A0In%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mkgandhi.org%2Febks%2Fhind_swaraj.pdf%5C%22%3E%20%3Cem%3EHind%20Swaraj%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20strongly%20criticised%20the%20concept%20of%20an%20independence%20that%20would%20merely%20be%20%E2%80%98English%20rule%20without%20the%20Englishman%E2%80%99.%20Similarly%2C%20Ambedkar%20recognised%20that%20caste%20oppression%20involves%20not%20just%20socioeconomic%20and%20political%20violence%2C%20but%20psychic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20retrospect%2C%20we%20can%20see%20that%20psychic%20violence%20is%20also%20far%20more%20insidious%20and%20difficult%20to%20escape%20than%20socioeconomic%20or%20political%20violence.%20Thus%2C%20despite%20India%20having%20been%20free%20for%20more%20than%2070%20years%20now%2C%20many%20Indians%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20Indian%20elites%2C%20but%20not%20only%20them%20%E2%80%93%20still%20yearn%20for%20the%20approval%20of%20%E2%80%9Cwestern%E2%80%9D%20authorities%20for%20%E2%80%9CIndian%E2%80%9D%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felections-2024-india-most-dangerous-phase%5C%22%3EAs%20the%202024%20Elections%20Approach%2C%20India%20Is%20Entering%20the%20Most%20Dangerous%20Phase%20of%20Its%20Existence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E**%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20psychic%20violence%20is%20inseparable%20from%20epistemic%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20the%20violence%20that%20occurs%20when%20knowledge%20about%20a%20subject%20is%20organised%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20it%20systematically%20silences%20or%20obliterates%20the%20very%20groups%20it%20targets%2C%20usually%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F467896581%2FAn-Introduction-to-Epistemic-Violence-Abhay-Xaxa%5C%22%3EAbhay%20Xaxa%20notes%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20%E2%80%9Ca%20denial%20of%20legitimacy%2C%20dignity%20or%20self%20respect%20to%20the%20groups%20it%20is%20targeted%20at.%E2%80%9D%20Epistemic%20violence%20inevitably%20accompanies%20and%20enables%20all%20domination%2C%20and%20colonial%20rule%20is%20one%20specially%20powerful%20systematisation%20of%20epistemic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEpistemic%20violence%20usually%20begins%20externally.%20But%20epistemic%20violence%20also%20becomes%20psychic%20violence%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20the%20colonised%2C%20and%20the%20dominated%2C%20all%20too%20often%20%E2%80%93%20though%20not%20always%20%E2%80%93%20internalise%20the%20language%20and%20categories%20of%20the%20dominant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20examples%20might%20help%20illustrate%20what%20I%20mean.%20The%20discourse%20of%20development%20in%20post-independence%20India%20involved%20an%20epistemic%20violence%20of%20both%20form%20and%20content%3A%20development%20as%20a%20form%20involves%20assuming%20that%20socioeconomic%20well-being%20involves%20a%20modernity%20based%20on%20the%20industrial%20domination%20of%20nature%2C%20and%20development%20as%20content%20involves%20a%20waiting%20room%20theory%20of%20history%2C%20where%20countries%20like%20India%20are%20constantly%20behind%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20heart%2C%20however%2C%20epistemic%20violence%20is%20more%20about%20form%20than%20content%2C%20sometimes%20even%20infusing%20the%20same%20form%20with%20content%20antithetical%20to%20that%20which%20the%20oppressors%20ascribe%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2019th%20and%20early%2020th%20century%2C%20thus%2C%20before%20the%20language%20of%20development%20displaced%20it%2C%20there%20was%20the%20language%20of%20civilisations.%20In%20Eurocentric%20thought%2C%20Europe%20was%20clearly%20the%20highest%20civilisation.%20Many%20Indian%20thinkers%20(Vivekananda%20comes%20to%20mind%20most%20readily)%20adopted%20this%20form.%20However%2C%20they%20insisted%20that%20while%20the%20West%20was%20a%20materialist%20civilisation%2C%20India%20as%20a%20spiritual%20civilisation%20held%20a%20higher%20stature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20is%20the%20case%20with%20the%20epistemic%20violence%20of%20caste.%20Those%20amongst%20the%20oppressed%20castes%20who%20acquiesced%20in%20their%20subordinate%20position%20accepted%20both%20the%20form%20and%20the%20content%20of%20the%20Brahmanical%20order.%20By%20contrast%2C%20%E2%80%9CSanskritisation%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20the%20adoption%20of%20Brahmanical%20values%20by%20the%20oppressed%20castes%2C%20enabled%20them%20to%20challenge%20the%20actual%20dominance%20of%20Brahmins%2C%20but%20left%20the%20form%20of%20the%20Brahmanical%20order%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E**%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHindutva%20is%20an%20especially%20illuminating%20example%20of%20the%20tortuous%20forms%20that%20epistemic%20violence%20can%20take.%20In%20terms%20of%20knowledge%2C%20it%20sees%20itself%20as%20a%20return%20to%20Indian%20traditions.%20In%20Fanon%E2%80%99s%20terms%2C%20we%20might%20even%20say%20that%20it%20is%20seeking%20to%20restore%20a%20%E2%80%9Clocal%20cultural%20originality%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20why%20it%20truly%20believes%20itself%20to%20be%20decolonialising%20India%20more%20thoroughly%20than%20the%20secular%20tradition%20ever%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20strange%20happens%20in%20this%20process%2C%20however.%20In%20the%20very%20process%20of%20seeking%20this%20local%20cultural%20originality%2C%20it%20enslaves%20itself%20to%20a%20Eurocentric%20epistemology%2C%20for%20it%20is%20that%20epistemology%20which%20produces%20the%20very%20distinctions%20and%20categories%20that%20Hindutva%20works%20with%3A%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20as%20monolithic%20and%20inimical%20communities%2C%20Indian%20civilisation%20as%20continuous%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20While%20attempting%20to%20free%20itself%20from%20Eurocentrism%2C%20it%20becomes%20a%20self-imposed%20slavish%20reproduction%20of%20the%20form%20of%20Eurocentrism%2C%20even%20if%20this%20form%20is%20imbued%20with%20new%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHindutva%20is%2C%20thus%2C%20the%20site%20of%20a%20doubled%20epistemic%20violence.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20it%20works%20with%20a%20certain%20vision%20of%20Muslims%2C%20Dalits%2C%20and%20Adivasis%2C%20especially%2C%20on%20whom%20it%20inflicts%20an%20enormous%20epistemic%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20quite%20apart%20from%20all%20the%20other%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20as%20it%20tries%20to%20realise%20this%20vision.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20this%20vision%20is%20itself%20the%20result%20of%2C%20or%20maybe%20the%20corollary%20of%2C%20a%20profoundly%20impoverished%20vision%20of%20Hindu%20traditions%20that%20it%20presumes%20constitute%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Hindutva%20is%20constituted%20most%20of%20all%20by%20an%20immense%20violence%20towards%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20towards%20those%20who%20have%20come%20to%20call%20themselves%20Hindus%20by%20its%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECenturies%20earlier%2C%20whiteness%20was%20fashioned%20by%20a%20similar%20internal%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20both%20psychological%20and%20epistemic%20%E2%80%93%20towards%20those%20who%20now%20call%20themselves%20white.%20Hence%2C%20Fanon%E2%80%99s%20remark%20that%20the%20white%20man%20is%20desperately%20trying%20to%20achieve%20the%20rank%20of%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20might%20go%20a%20little%20further%3A%20even%20if%20the%20oppressed%20suffer%20more%20in%20material%20and%20political%20terms%2C%20the%20oppressors%20are%20structurally%20at%20least%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20psychic%20violence%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20they%20suffer%20more%20or%20less%20of%20it.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20oppressed%20can%20at%20least%20in%20principle%20(though%20it%20is%20very%20hard%20in%20practice%2C%20as%20both%20Gandhi%20and%20Ambedkar%20in%20different%20ways%20realised)%20sidestep%20or%20step%20back%20from%20the%20psychological%20dimension%20of%20the%20violence%20that%20the%20oppressors%20inflict%20on%20them.%20By%20contrast%2C%20oppression%20involves%20inflicting%20psychological%20violence%20on%20oneself%3B%20it%20involves%20becoming%20incapable%20of%20staying%20non-privatively%20with%20our%20vulnerabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-hindutva-is-a-racist-supremacism-not-a-communalism-or-majoritarianism%5C%22%3EWhy%20Hindutva%20Is%20a%20Racist%20Supremacism%20%E2%80%93%20Not%20Merely%20Communalism%20or%20Majoritarianism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E**%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20might%20the%20oppressed%20liberate%20themselves%20from%20themselves%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20to%20say%2C%20from%20psychic%20violence%3F%20This%20is%20the%20question%20that%20follows%20from%20Fanon%E2%80%99s%20aim%20to%20liberate%20the%20black%20man%20from%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20modernity%2C%20the%20most%20common%20answer%20has%20been%20that%20the%20oppressed%20should%20return%20to%20some%20local%20cultural%20originality.%20Hindutva%20and%20white%20nationalism%20are%20especially%20zealous%20iterations%20of%20this%20answer.%20But%20some%20version%20of%20the%20same%20answer%20runs%20through%20even%20mainstream%20nationalist%20movements%2C%20such%20as%20that%20led%20by%20the%20Congress%20in%2020th%20century%20India%20%E2%80%93%20what%20else%20is%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20as%20an%20eternal%20or%20continuous%20civilisation%20but%20the%20assertion%20of%20an%20inextirpable%20local%20cultural%20originality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20answer%20can%20never%20succeed%20in%20realising%20itself%2C%20because%20there%20is%20no%20local%20cultural%20originality%20to%20return%20to%20%E2%80%93%20that%20originality%20is%20itself%20the%20product%20of%20the%20reification%20that%20constitutes%20the%20dominant%20forms%20of%20our%20modernity.%20There%20are%20only%20everywhere%20the%20messy%20relations%20of%20the%20pre-modern%20world%20%E2%80%93%20as%20messy%20as%20those%20of%20the%20modern%20world%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20when%20we%20let%20go%20of%20our%20reifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E**%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20else%20then%20might%20the%20oppressed%20liberate%20themselves%20from%20themselves%3F%20Fanon%20himself%20has%20a%20very%20distinctive%20answer%3A%20%E2%80%9CMan%20is%20not%20only%20the%20potential%20for%20self-consciousness%20or%20negation.%20If%20it%20is%20true%20that%20consciousness%20is%20transcendental%2C%20we%20must%20also%20realise%20that%20this%20transcendence%20is%20obsessed%20with%20the%20issue%20of%20love%20and%20understanding.%20Man%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cyes%E2%80%9D%20resonating%20from%20cosmic%20harmonies.%20Uprooted%2C%20dispersed%2C%20dazed%2C%20and%20doomed%20to%20watch%20as%20the%20truths%20he%20has%20elaborated%20vanish%20one%20by%20one%2C%20he%20must%20stop%20projecting%20his%20antinomy%20into%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20passage%20steps%20back%20from%20so%20much%20so%20crisply%3A%20from%20Hegel%E2%80%99s%20emphasis%20on%20a%20transcendental%20consciousness%20arrived%20at%20through%20negation%2C%20from%20the%20Marxist%20tradition%20of%20dialectics%2C%20negative%20or%20not%2C%20from%20the%20psychoanalytic%20scepticism%20of%20love.%20And%20it%20affirms%20a%20world%20too%20%E2%80%93%20the%20world%20of%20love%20and%20understanding%2C%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cyes%E2%80%9D%20resonating%20from%20cosmic%20harmonies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20in%20what%20Fanon%20draws%20back%20from%20and%20in%20what%20he%20affirms%2C%20we%20can%20find%20allies%20for%20him%20both%20in%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20%E2%80%93%20Gandhi%20and%20Ambedkar%2C%20and%20Iqbal%2C%20most%20evidently%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20including%20Hannah%20Arendt%2C%20James%20Baldwin%2C%20Martin%20Luther%20King%2C%20Audre%20Lorde%20and%20Simone%20Weil.%20What%20they%20all%20share%20is%20a%20desire%20to%20not%20only%20oppose%20socioeconomic%20and%20political%20violence%2C%20but%20to%20also%20to%20liberate%20themselves%20and%20others%20from%20the%20sociopolitical%20forms%20of%20psychic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20has%20been%20written%20about%20these%20thinkers%20and%20actors.%20But%20the%20vistas%20they%20open%20up%20are%20immense%2C%20and%20much%20of%20what%20they%20and%20others%20of%20their%20ilk%20have%20thought%20and%20done%20and%20initiated%20remains%20to%20be%20explored%20further.%20If%20we%20are%20to%20think%20with%20them%2C%20think%20otherwise%20with%20them%2C%20then%20we%20must%20think%20of%20both%20the%20sociopolitical%20forms%20of%20psychic%20violence%2C%20and%20the%20ways%20which%20we%20have%20and%20might%20resist%20such%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjay%20Skaria%20teaches%20history%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704184243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F04152208%2FScreenshot-2023-09-04-at-3.21.24.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fliberation-from-psychic-violence-understanding-the-psychological-dimension-of-domination%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unlike%20socioeconomic%20and%20political%20colonialism%20and%20violence%2C%20which%20can%20remain%20primarily%20external%2C%20psychic%20violence%20embeds%20itself%20in%20the%20soul.%20And%20it%20embeds%20itself%20in%20the%20soul%20of%20both%20the%20oppressor%20and%20the%20oppressed.%20So%2C%20it%20dehumanises%20not%20only%20the%20oppressed%20but%20also%20the%20oppressor.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fliberation-from-psychic-violence-understanding-the-psychological-dimension-of-domin