%3Cp%3ERiverdale%20Police%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20said%20Zhuang%20was%20a%20victim%20of%20%26quot%3Bcyber%20kidnapping%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20ploy%20to%20convince%20families%20to%20pay%20a%20ransom%20over%20a%20kidnapping%20that%20never%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScammers%20often%20target%20Chinese%20foreign%20exchange%20students%2C%20who%20are%20contacted%20via%20FaceTime%20or%20Skype%20and%20told%20to%20follow%20instructions%20or%20risk%20their%20families%20being%20threatened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20students%20are%20ordered%20to%20isolate%20themselves%20and%20send%20photos%20depicting%20themselves%20as%20captives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20criminals%20then%20send%20the%20photos%20to%20the%20victim's%20family%20with%20a%20ransom%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cyberkidnappers%20continue%20to%20extort%20the%20family%20by%20using%20fear%2C%20tactics%2C%20photos%2C%20and%20voice%20recordings%20of%20the%20victim%2C%20leading%20the%20family%20to%20believe%20the%20kidnappers%20are%20with%20the%20victim%20causing%20them%20harm%2C%26quot%3B%20Riverdale%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20exactly%20what%20happened%20to%20Zhuang%20and%20his%20parents%2C%20the%20police%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EZhuang%20tried%20to%20camp%20alone%20twice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZhuang%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20initially%20been%20told%20to%20camp%20by%20himself%20away%20from%20his%20host%20family%20in%20Riverdale%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20tried%20to%20follow%20those%20instructions%20on%20December%2020%2C%20per%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20in%20Provo%2C%20a%20city%20to%20the%20south%20of%20Salt%20Lake%20City%2C%20found%20Zhuang%20that%20day%20carrying%20camping%20equipment.%20The%20officers%20didn't%20know%20Zhuang%20was%20under%20duress%2C%20and%20took%20him%20back%20to%20his%20host%20family%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20left%20his%20host%20family%20again%20shortly%20after%2C%20and%20on